Officials say the mayor was admitted to the Helen Joseph Hospital on Saturday morning. JOHANNESBURG – Mogale city mayor Patrick Lipudi has died. Officials say the mayor was admitted to the Helen Joseph Hospital on Saturday morning. He died this morning after a short illness. Lipudi was 59. Chief administrator in the officer of the mayor Sabelo Ngwane said, “I can confirm that it was a natural death because there was no accident. I can’t say what exactly was the cause.”